<dl id="n12094b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12094b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12094b"> 94(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hairpins in bed</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les trois premi&egrave;res nuits, &agrave; la campagne, les nouveaux mari&eacute;s couchent dans la demeure de la jeune fille; souvent ils trouvent les draps du lit d&eacute;rang&eacute;s, ou parsem&eacute;s de miettes de pain, de cheveux ou de crins. <br><font color="green">[The first three nights, in the country-side, the newly-weds sleep at the girl&apos;s house; often they&apos;ll find the bedclothes in disarray, or sprinkled with bread crumbs, hairs or bristles.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="RDTP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RDTP"><cite title="source">Traditions et coutumes de Basse Bretagne</cite></a> (1904) 355</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
